# Add more properties to operation plans
noria:OperationPlan_DiskCleanup
    dcterms:description "This procedure outlines steps to identify and remove unnecessary files to free up disk space on database servers, ensuring optimal performance and preventing outages."@en .

noria:OperationPlan_InterfaceTroubleshooting
    dcterms:description "This guide provides a systematic approach to diagnose and resolve common issues affecting network interface operational status, including physical layer checks and configuration verification."@en .

# Add more properties to pre/post conditions
noria:ActionPreCondition_DiskFull
    dcterms:description "A critical alert is triggered when the disk space on a database server reaches 90% or more of its total capacity, indicating an imminent risk of service interruption."@en .

noria:ActionPostCondition_DiskSpaceFreed
    dcterms:description "Successful execution of the disk cleanup procedure is confirmed when the disk utilization drops below 80%, restoring a healthy operational margin."@en .

noria:ActionPreCondition_InterfaceDown
    dcterms:description "The network monitoring system reports an interface as 'down', indicating a loss of connectivity or a physical fault on the network device."@en .

noria:ActionPostCondition_InterfaceUp
    dcterms:description "The network interface's operational status is verified to be 'up' and stable, confirming restoration of connectivity."@en .

