# Final check for connectivity and density:
# - All Resources are managed by an Agent, have a ProductModel, Type, UsageState, and are located.
# - All NetworkInterfaces are part of a Resource and connect to a NetworkLink.
# - All NetworkLinks connect Resources and Interfaces.
# - All Applications have Type, BusinessImportance, and are linked to Resources.
# - All ApplicationModules are part of an Application and have status/teams.
# - All Services are composed of Applications/Resources.
# - All TroubleTickets are linked to Services/Applications/Resources, Agents, and EventRecords.
# - All TroubleTicketNotes are linked to TroubleTickets.
# - All ChangeRequests are linked to Applications/Resources, Agents, and have planned times.
# - All EventRecords originate from ManagedObjects/ManagementSystems/Agents and have logging time/text.
# - OperationPlans have Pre/PostConditions.
# - AnomalyPatterns are linked to detection/mitigation.
# - Many entities have labels, comments, and identifiers.
# - KOS concepts are used correctly.
# - All entities are interconnected.

# This graph is now quite dense and covers a wide range of NORIA concepts.
